text: Hey Zachary, 1/4" acrylic is kind of tricky because it gets hot and a bit melty when there are a bunch of cuts this close together. We cut it out, but the whole piece deformed as we were removing it - so none of the tolerances will be correct. If you want to make sure that they're roughly the right size (i.e. you converted the file correctly), the piece is outside. Otherwise for specific tolerancing, you can make a test piece with a bit more space between the cuts

elements.text: Hey Zachary, 1/4" acrylic is kind of tricky because it gets hot and a bit melty when there are a bunch of cuts this close together. We cut it out, but the whole piece deformed as we were removing it - so none of the tolerances will be correct. If you want to make sure that they're roughly the right size (i.e. you converted the file correctly), the piece is outside. Otherwise for specific tolerancing, you can make a test piece with a bit more space between the cuts
